sentence: Among the underlying components of the S&P 500 index, we saw noteworthy options trading volume today in Home Depot Inc (Symbol: HD), where a total of 36,509 contracts have traded so far, representing approximately 3.7 million underlying shares.
That amounts to about 78.9% of HD's average daily trading volume over the past month of 4.6 million shares.
Especially high volume was seen for the $180 strike call option expiring May 18, 2018 , with 2,249 contracts trading so far today, representing approximately 224,900 underlying shares of HD.

Time Warner Inc (Symbol: TWX) saw options trading volume of 36,721 contracts, representing approximately 3.7 million underlying shares or approximately 70.7% of TWX's average daily trading volume over the past month, of 5.2 million shares.
Especially high volume was seen for the $95 strike call option expiring July 20, 2018 , with 10,353 contracts trading so far today, representing approximately 1.0 million underlying shares of TWX.

Below is a chart showing TWX's trailing twelve month trading history, with the $95 strike highlighted in orange:

And United Parcel Service Inc (Symbol: UPS) saw options trading volume of 23,575 contracts, representing approximately 2.4 million underlying shares or approximately 68.6% of UPS's average daily trading volume over the past month, of 3.4 million shares.
Particularly high volume was seen for the $120 strike call option expiring January 18, 2019 , with 1,536 contracts trading so far today, representing approximately 153,600 underlying shares of UPS.
